{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:job.28",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 28,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 28",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 28 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.28.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:1",
      "text": "Surely there is a vein for the silver, and a place for gold where they fine it.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.28.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:2",
      "text": "Iron is taken out of the earth, and brass is molten out of the stone.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.28.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:3",
      "text": "He setteth an end to darkness, and searcheth out all perfection: the stones of darkness, and the shadow of death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.28.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:4",
      "text": "The flood breaketh out from the inhabitant; even the waters forgotten of the foot: they are dried up, they are gone away from men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.28.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:5",
      "text": "As for the earth, out of it cometh bread: and under it is turned up as it were fire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.28.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:6",
      "text": "The stones of it are the place of sapphires: and it hath dust of gold.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.28.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:7",
      "text": "There is a path which no fowl knoweth, and which the vulture’s eye hath not seen:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.28.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:8",
      "text": "The lion’s whelps have not trodden it, nor the fierce lion passed by it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.28.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:9",
      "text": "He putteth forth his hand upon the rock; he overturneth the mountains by the roots.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.28.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:10",
      "text": "He cutteth out rivers among the rocks; and his eye seeth every precious thing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.28.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:11",
      "text": "He bindeth the floods from overflowing; and the thing that is hid bringeth he forth to light.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.28.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:12",
      "text": "But where shall wisdom be found? and where is the place of understanding?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.28.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:13",
      "text": "Man knoweth not the price thereof; neither is it found in the land of the living.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.28.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:14",
      "text": "The depth saith, It is not in me: and the sea saith, It is not with me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.28.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:15",
      "text": "It cannot be gotten for gold, neither shall silver be weighed for the price thereof.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.28.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:16",
      "text": "It cannot be valued with the gold of Ophir, with the precious onyx, or the sapphire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.28.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:17",
      "text": "The gold and the crystal cannot equal it: and the exchange of it shall not be for jewels of fine gold.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.28.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:18",
      "text": "No mention shall be made of coral, or of pearls: for the price of wisdom is above rubies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.28.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:19",
      "text": "The topaz of Ethiopia shall not equal it, neither shall it be valued with pure gold.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.28.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:20",
      "text": "Whence then cometh wisdom? and where is the place of understanding?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.28.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:21",
      "text": "Seeing it is hid from the eyes of all living, and kept close from the fowls of the air.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.28.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:22",
      "text": "Destruction and death say, We have heard the fame thereof with our ears.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.28.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:23",
      "text": "God understandeth the way thereof, and he knoweth the place thereof.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.28.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:24",
      "text": "For he looketh to the ends of the earth, and seeth under the whole heaven;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.28.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:25",
      "text": "To make the weight for the winds; and he weigheth the waters by measure.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.28.26",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:26",
      "text": "When he made a decree for the rain, and a way for the lightning of the thunder:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.28.27",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:27",
      "text": "Then did he see it, and declare it; he prepared it, yea, and searched it out.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.28.28",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:28",
      "text": "And unto man he said, Behold, the fear of the Lord, that is wisdom; and to depart from evil is understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
